{
  "doc_id": "35139",
  "text": "In typically developing individuals, the prefrontal cortex has been associated with the attribution of a mental state or \"theory of mind\" to another person [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Individuals with ASD have been found to have mental state or \"theory of mind\" deficit [CITATION_3] ) associated with reduced activation in the prefrontal cortex [CITATION_4] . However, in a recent study high-functioning individuals with ASD, who were less accurate than controls, did not have significantly different prefrontal activations when asked to explicitly attribute emotion from basic facial expressions [CITATION_5] .",
